{"TopicId":3268,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Escape Velocity","CreatedByName":"JupiterII","CreatedById":8029,"CreatedDateTime":"2011-10-28T19:33:36Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"JupiterII","CreatedById":8029,"CreatedDateTime":"2011-10-28T19:33:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EAll you need are 4 fuel tanks and a liquid engine.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Ciframe width=\u0022459\u0022 height=\u0022344\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/tJvF8aG9zSw?feature=oembed\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"derhp","CreatedById":8166,"CreatedDateTime":"2011-10-28T22:42:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI challenge you to do it with three. I\\\u0027m sure you can make it work, though it might require a TURN in your thinking \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JupiterII","CreatedById":8029,"CreatedDateTime":"2011-10-29T01:17:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Ciframe width=\u0022459\u0022 height=\u0022344\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/dnrWTk49D4g?feature=oembed\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"derhp","CreatedById":8166,"CreatedDateTime":"2011-10-29T01:32:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EWell done. Though I was referring to the fact you get a bit of a boost if you burn horizontally at around 12000m. I\\\u0027m genuinely surprised that it could be done with a direct ascent.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JupiterII","CreatedById":8029,"CreatedDateTime":"2011-10-29T01:33:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquo